# Terminal: Git Bash Only

When suggesting or writing terminal commands for this project, **always use Git Bash (bash/sh) syntax**, not PowerShell or CMD.

## Do

- Use `&&` to chain commands: `cd backend && php artisan serve`
- Use forward slashes in paths: `./start.sh`, `backend/.env`
- Use `export VAR=value` for environment variables
- Use `./script.sh` to run scripts
- Use Unix-style: `npm run dev`, `docker compose up -d`

## Don't

- Don't use PowerShell: `Set-Location`, `;`, `.\script.ps1`
- Don't use CMD: `cd /d`, `&&` with different semantics
- Don't use PowerShell env: `$env:VAR = "value"`

## Examples

| Intent        | Use (Git Bash)           | Not (PowerShell)              |
|---------------|--------------------------|-------------------------------|
| Change dir    | `cd backend`             | `Set-Location backend`        |
| Chain commands| `cd backend && php artisan migrate` | `Set-Location backend; php artisan migrate` |
| Run script    | `./start.sh`                     | `.\start.ps1`           |
| Env var       | `export APP_URL=http://localhost:8201` | `$env:APP_URL = "..."` |

When the user runs commands in their terminal, assume they use **Git Bash**.
